  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Previous studies have shown that alcohol significantly impairs driving performance. Acute
      alcohol administration also has a detrimental effect on secondary task performance during
      dual-tasks. The present study will investigate the effects of five different dosages of
      ethanol (0,0.2, 0,5, 0,8 and 1,0 % BAC) on performance in a driving simulator. Steering
      performance and brain activity will be recorded in both single- and dual-task conditions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
